sp;ft\n| 2 [[GE Passport]]\t|| {{#expr:2*18920}} lbf\t|| 114,850&nbsp;lb\t|| 7,725&nbsp;nmi\t|| 475 kn\t|| {{#expr:48519/7725round2}} lb\n|}\n\n===VIP airliners ===\n\n[[File:Boeing's commercial aircraft in BBJ livery.jpg|thumb|[[Boeing Business Jet]]s are the most widespread bizliners.]]\n\n''Business airliner'' can be contracted as ''bizliner''.<ref name=\"AIN\">{{cite web |url= http://www.ainonline.com/aviation-news/business-aviation/2010-06-17/airbus-sees-great-promise-bizliner-orders-china |title= Airbus Sees Great Promise for Bizliner Orders in China |publisher= [[Aviation International News]] |author=Chad Trautvetter |date= 17 June 2010}}</ref> [[Airliner]]s converted into business jets are used by sports teams or [[VIP]]s with a large entourage or press corps. Such airplanes can face operational restrictions based on runway length or local [[noise restriction]]s. They can be the most expensive type of private jet as they provide the greatest space and capabilities.\n\nAircraft of this class include:\n* [[Airbus Corporate Jets]]<ref name=AP/><ref name=JA/><ref name=AC/><ref name=BAP/>\n* [[Boeing Business Jet]]<ref name=AP/><ref name=JA/><ref name=AC/><ref name=BAP/>\n* [[Embraer Lineage 1000]]<ref name=AP/><ref name=JA/>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+ VIP Airliners, 8 pax mission<ref name=PPH1805>{{cite news |url= http://aviationweek.com/site-files/aviationweek.com/files/datasheets/gated/BCA_201805.pdf |title= 2018 Business Airplanes Purchase Planning Handbook |work= Business & Commercial Aviation |publisher= Aviation Week |date= May 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n! Model !! Pax !! Length !! Span !! int. L !! int. W\n! Engines !! Thrust !! MTOW !! Range !! Cruise !! Fuel/nmi\n|-\n| [[Embraer Lineage 1000|Lineage 1000]]E\t|| 13\u201319\t|| 118.9&nbsp;ft\t|| 94.2&nbsp;ft\t|| 84.3&nbsp;ft\t|| 8.8&nbsp;ft\t|| 2 [[General Electric CF34|CF34]]\t|| {{#expr:2*18500}} lb\t|| 120,152&nbsp;lb\t|| 4,602&nbsp;nmi{{efn|name=4pax}}\t|| 446 kn\t|| {{#expr:44240/4602round2}} lb\n