University of Mainz]]<br /><small>Gutenberg School of Management & Economics ([[Master of Economics|M.S.]])</small>\n|profession=[[Politician]]\n|residence = [[Sangam-dong]], [[Mapo-gu]]<br />[[Seoul|Seoul metropolitan city]]<br />[[South Korea]]\n|occupation = \n|religion = \n|signature = Ryu Si-min signature.png\n|website = [http://www.usimin.net/ Official website in Korean]\n|allegiance       = {{flag|South Korea}}\n|branch           = {{flagicon image|Flag_of_the_Army_of_the_Republic_of_Korea.svg}} [[Republic of Korea Army]]\n|serviceyears     = 1980-1983\n|rank             = [[File:ROK Army Byeongjang.png|24px]] [[Byeongjang]]\n| module        = {{Infobox Korean name\n|hangul= {{linktext|\uc720|\uc2dc|\ubbfc}}\n|hanja={{linktext|\u67f3|\u6642|\u654f}}\n|rr= Yu Simin\n|mr= Yu Simin\n| child  = yes}}\n}}\n\n'''Rhyu Si-min''' ({{Ko-hhrm|hangul=\uc720\uc2dc\ubbfc}}; born July 28, 1959)  is a [[South Korea]]n politician who served as the 44th [[Ministry of Health and Welfare (South Korea)|Minister of Health and Welfare]] from February 2006 to May 2007. Before starting his political career since August 2002, he was a journalist of ''[[Dong-a Ilbo]]'' and ''[[The Hankyoreh]]'', with having his continuous [[Progressivism|progressive]] and [[Liberalism|liberal]] attitudes. He was in the [[United New Democratic Party|UNDP]] as an [[National Assembly of South Korea|Assembly member]] (representative) for [[Deogyang-gu|Deogyang]] A district, and is a graduate of [[Seoul National University]] with a degree in [[Economics]], and master's from the [[Johannes Gutenberg University of Mainz]] in [[Economics]]. He resigned on May 22, 2007. He declared his [[2007 South Korean presidential election|presidential candidacy]] on August 18, 2007.<ref>[http://www.usimin.net/3/bbs/tb.php/USM_TALK/697 (Press-release)Rhyu Si-min officially announced his pre-registered candidacy for the 2007 presidential election], Usimin.net, Retrieved on August 21, 2007</ref>\n\nHe was selected by the liberal opposition parties to run for governor of [[Gyeonggi-do]] province on May 13, 2010 <ref>[http://joongangdaily.joins.com/article/view.asp?aid=2920407 Opposition bloc fields joint candidate for Gyeonggi governor], JoongAng Daily, Retrieved on May 25, 2010</ref> In December 2011, Rhyu merged his [[People's Participation Party]] into the [[Unified Progressive Party]], of which he is one of the co-chairs.<ref>{{Citation |url=http://app.yonhapnews.co.kr/YNA/Basic/ArticleEnglish/ArticlePhoto/YIBW_new_showArticlePhotoView.aspx?contents_id=PYH20111205016000341&PAGINGCURRENTPAGE=17 |title=Progressive parties unified |publisher=Yonhap News Agency |accessdate=1 February 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120707200444/http://app.yonhapnews.co.kr/YNA/Basic/ArticleEnglish/ArticlePhoto/YIBW_new_showArticlePhotoView.aspx?contents_id=PYH20111205016000341&PAGINGCURRENTPAGE=17 |archivedate=7 July 2012 }}</ref>\n\nHe announced his retirement from politics on February 19, 2013.<ref>[http://news.khan.co.kr/kh_news/khan_art_view.html?artid=201302192220135&code=910402 The Kyunghyang Shinmun] 2013 February 19</ref>\n\n==Career==\nAfter graduating [https://web.archive.org/web/20010227052633/http://www.simin.hs.kr/ Shim-in Senior High(School)] in [[Daegu]], he entered [[Seoul National University]] and served as president of the Students' Union in the 1980s. He fought against [[Chun Doo-hwan]]'s military regime to bring freedom and democracy to his nation, however, he was arrested with an accusation (the SNU Fraction case, which was made by Chun's regime) and enlisted to the DMZ to serve a military service for 33 months. He has become popular in a field of the Democratic movement of South Korea, with claiming his false-charge with '[http://www.usimin.net/3/bbs/tb.php/USM_BOOK/648 The grounds of an appeal]'(\ud56d\uc18c\uc774\uc720\uc11c) against the Seoul district court which secured by Chun's regime.<ref>[http://h21.hani.co.kr/section-021075000/2005/04/021075000200504040554052.html Do not become sensible like Rhyu Si-min](Korean), Prof. Dr.Han Hong-gu, [[The Hankyoreh|Hankyoreh]] 21, Retrieved on April 4, 2005</ref>\n\nAfter the 1987 election, he married his colleague, Dr. Han Gyeong-hye (\ud55c\uacbd\ud61c), an SNU graduate in Mathematics (and a fellow of Democratic movement) on November 1988, and served as an aide to [[Lee Hae Chan]] (a [[Korean National Assembly|Member]] at that moment) for 2 years. After finishing his job, the couple went to Germany to study their majors in the 1990s.<ref>[http://www.jejusori.net/news/articleView.html?idxno=36042#69665 My husband is the most-domestic person], an Interview with Dr. Han Gyeong-hye, Voice of Jeju, Retrieved on August 29, 2007</ref>\n\nHe has predicted that a gigantic scandal affiliated to the [[Lee Myung-bak government]] will be eventually publicized due to the two elections in 2012.<ref>{{cite news | script-title=ko:\uc720\uc2dc\ubbfc \"\ucd1d\uc120 \uc5ec\uc18c\uc57c\ub300 \ub418\uba74 \uc0c1\uc0c1\ucd08\uc6d4 \ucd08\ub300\ud615 \uc815\uad8c \ube44\ub9ac \ud130\uc9c8 \uac83\" | date = 2012-02-01 | url = http://www.nocutnews.co.kr/show.asp?idx=2046220 | work = Nocut News | accessdate = 2012-03-14 | language = Korean}}</ref>\n\nSince 2019, Rhyu has been the host of a YouTube show and podcast called \"Alileo\" which literally means \"I want you to know\".\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.usimin.net Official Homepage] {{in lang|ko}}\n* [http://www.usimin.co.kr Simin Gwangjang(\uc2dc\ubbfc\uad11\uc7a5, Official political initiative)]{{in lang|ko}}\n* [http://cafe.daum.net/siminyoo Simin Sarang(\uc2dc\ubbfc\uc0ac\ub791, Official on-line fanpage)] {{in lang|ko}}\n* [http://cafe.daum.net/siminlov Simin Maul(\uc2dc\ubbfc\ub9c8\uc744, Online fanpage)] {{in lang|ko}}\n* [http://cafe.daum.net/newsimin Newsimin(\ub274 \uc2dc\ubbfc, On-line fanpage)] {{in lang|ko}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-off}}\n{{succession box\n|before=[[Kim Geun Tae]]\n|after=Byun Jae-jin\n|